                    Specify <span class="emphasis"><em>x</em></span>, <span class="emphasis"><em>y</em></span>, <span class="emphasis"><em>z</em></span>, and <span class="emphasis"><em>w</em></span> coordinates of a vertex.
                    Not all parameters are present in all forms of the command.
                </p></dd></dl></div></div><div class="refsynopsisdiv"><h2>C Specification</h2><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef"> void <b class="fsfunc">glVertex2sv</b>(</code><var class="pdparam">v</var><code>)</code>;<br /> const GLshort * <var class="pdparam">v</var>;</p></div><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef"> void <b class="fsfunc">glVertex2iv</b>(</code><var class="pdparam">v</var><code>)</code>;<br /> const GLint * <var class="pdparam">v</var>;</p></div><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef"> void <b class="fsfunc">glVertex2fv</b>(</code><var class="pdparam">v</var><code>)</code>;<br /> const GLfloat * <var class="pdparam">v</var>;</p></div><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef"> void <b class="fsfunc">glVertex2dv</b>(</code><var class="pdparam">v</var><code>)</code>;<br /> const GLdouble * <var class="pdparam">v</var>;</p></div><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef"> void <b class="fsfunc">glVertex3sv</b>(</code><var class="pdparam">v</var><code>)</code>;<br /> const GLshort * <var class="pdparam">v</var>;</p></div><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef"> void <b class="fsfunc">glVertex3iv</b>(</code><var class="pdparam">v</var><code>)</code>;<br /> const GLint * <var class="pdparam">v</var>;</p></div><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef"> void <b class="fsfunc">glVertex3fv</b>(</code><var class="pdparam">v</var><code>)</code>;<br /> const GLfloat * <var class="pdparam">v</var>;</p></div><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef"> void <b class="fsfunc">glVertex3dv</b>(</code><var class="pdparam">v</var><code>)</code>;<br /> const GLdouble * <var class="pdparam">v</var>;</p></div><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef"> void <b class="fsfunc">glVertex4sv</b>(</code><var class="pdparam">v</var><code>)</code>;<br /> const GLshort * <var class="pdparam">v</var>;</p></div><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef"> void <b class="fsfunc">glVertex4iv</b>(</code><var class="pdparam">v</var><code>)</code>;<br /> const GLint * <var class="pdparam">v</var>;</p></div><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef"> void <b class="fsfunc">glVertex4fv</b>(</code><var class="pdparam">v</var><code>)</code>;<br /> const GLfloat * <var class="pdparam">v</var>;</p></div><div class="funcsynopsis"><p><code class="funcdef"> void <b class="fsfunc">glVertex4dv</b>(</code><var class="pdparam">v</var><code>)</code>;<br /> const GLdouble * <var class="pdparam">v</var>;</p></div></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4712854"></a><h2>Parameters</h2><div class="variablelist"><dl><dt><span class="term"><em class="parameter"><code>v</code></em></span></dt><dd><p>
                    Specifies a pointer to an array of two, three, or four elements.
                    The elements of a two-element array are 
                    <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">x</mml:mi></mml:math>
                    and 
                    <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">y</mml:mi></mml:math>;
                    of a three-element array, 
                    <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">x</mml:mi></mml:math>,
                    <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">y</mml:mi></mml:math>,
                    and 
                    <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">z</mml:mi></mml:math>;
                    and of a four-element array, 
                    <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">x</mml:mi></mml:math>,
                    <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">y</mml:mi></mml:math>,
                    <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">z</mml:mi></mml:math>,
                    and 
                    <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">w</mml:mi></mml:math>.
                </p></dd></dl></div></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4712998"></a><h2>Description</h2><p>
            <code class="function">glVertex</code> commands are used within <span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glBegin</span></span>/<span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glEnd</span></span> pairs to specify
            point, line, and polygon vertices.  The current color, normal, texture
            coordinates, and fog coordinate are associated with the vertex when <code class="function">glVertex</code>
            is called.
        </p><p>
            When only 
            <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">x</mml:mi></mml:math>
            and 
            <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">y</mml:mi></mml:math>
            are specified, 
            <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">z</mml:mi></mml:math>
            defaults to 0 and
            <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">w</mml:mi></mml:math>
            defaults to 1.  When 
            <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">x</mml:mi></mml:math>,
            <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">y</mml:mi></mml:math>,
            and 
            <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">z</mml:mi></mml:math>
            are specified, 
            <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi mathvariant="italic">w</mml:mi></mml:math>
            defaults to 1.
        </p></div><div class="refsect1" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><a id="id4713136"></a><h2>Notes</h2><p>
            Invoking <code class="function">glVertex</code> outside of a <span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glBegin</span></span>/<span class="citerefentry"><span class="refentrytitle">glEnd</span></span> pair
            results in undefined behavior.
